main event: An unidentified flying object was tracked on radar for 1 minute, displaying erratic motion and appearing solid.
interesting points: The object was detected on ground radar but lost on a separate radar scope., The duration of observation was only 1 minute., Observers described the object having an indefinite size and shape., Conclusions included radar lock-on and possible satellite identification., The object varied in altitude from about 5000 feet to 16000 feet during tracking.
witness description: Observers included both military personnel and civilians, with reliability deemed above suspicion.
